**Whispers of the Night**

In twilight's glow where shadows dance,  
The world unfolds in a whispered trance.  
Stars emerge like secrets spun,  
Beneath the watchful eye of the moon.  

Leaves rustle softly, a tender sigh,  
As nightingale songs weave through the sky.  
Gentle breezes carry the past,  
While dreams, like fireflies, flicker and cast.  

In the garden where memories bloom,  
Echoes of laughter dispel the gloom.  
Each petal tells tales of love once shared,  
Of hearts entwined and souls laid bare.  

The cool earth cradles the weight of time,  
While silence hums its sacred rhyme.  
A symphony played in soft, hushed tones,  
Whispers of all that our hearts have known.  

Time lingers here, in this sacred space,  
Where every shadow finds its place.  
As night deepens, so do our fears,  
Yet hope ignites through the veil of tears.  

So let us walk beneath the stars,  
Leave behind our silent scars.  
For in the darkness, light will spark,  
A promise born in the hidden dark.  

With every breath, we find our way,  
Embracing the night, welcoming the day.  
In the quiet, life unfolds anew,  
In whispers of the night, I find you.
